Open Standard License — SLANG-Computation Reference Implementation

SLANG-Computation — Structural Resolution (Computation Without Execution)
Shunyaya Structural Resolution Model

Legal Status

This license is a permissive Open Standard license for the SLANG-Computation reference implementation.

To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, this license grants rights similar in spirit to permissive open-source licenses, while preserving truthful representation requirements for the SLANG-Computation name and reference implementation.

If any provision is found unenforceable, the remaining provisions remain in effect.

Nature of Release

This is a minimal, self-contained reference implementation.

It is intended to demonstrate a structural correctness model—not to represent a complete programming language, runtime, or general-purpose computation system.

Behavioral guarantees apply only within the scope of the reference model.

